This Al Jazeera piece effectively combines clear mapping and concise metrics to convey why specific straits and channels are strategic. The visuals, location data, and oil-flow estimates make the stakes tangible (especially Hormuz, Malacca, and the Taiwan Strait). It is interactive, which is always good for data journalism articles. Weaknesses: the article relies heavily on top-line figures without sourcing or uncertainty ranges, and it treats “trade value” and “volume” interchangeably in places without clarifying methodology. To deepen the analysis the authors could add sourced time-series data on traffic and disruptions.  
